But given that Homo sapiens occupies its current level at the pinnacle of evolutionary achievement due to our intellectual capacity, which has allowed us to manipulate and adapt our environments to suit our needs, I find it impossible to state unequivocally that humans should have zero impact on the environment. To do so would have a severe impact on all societies world-wide. Rather, we need to adopt new technologies that allow us to thrive and grow, while having the least affect to the environment.
